  "prompt": "Is a passport compulsory to travel on flights within India?",
  "response": "No, a passport is not compulsory for traveling on domestic flights within India. Indian citizens can use any of the following valid identification documents for domestic air travel:\n\n1. **Aadhaar Card**  \n2. **Voter ID Card**  \n3. **PAN Card**  \n4. **Driving License**  \n5. **Passport** (though not compulsory)  \n6. **Permanent Account Number (PAN) Card**  \n7. **Employee ID** (issued by a central/state government or PSUs)  \n8. **Student ID** (issued by a recognized educational institution)  \n9. **Nationalized Bank Passbook with a photograph**  \n10. **Photo ID cards issued by the Ministry of Home Affairs**  \n\nMake sure the ID document is valid and matches the name on your flight ticket. For minors (under 18 years), a school ID or birth certificate may be accepted.\n\nCheck with your airline for specific requirements, as rules may vary slightly.",
